Moulinex S.A., a Paris-based maker of household electrical appliances, posted a 47% jump in first-half profit and said earnings for all of 1989 will exceed the 25% growth projected earlier. 

The company said profit for the six months was 47 million French francs ($7.4 million), compared with 32 million francs in the 1988 period.
Revenue rose 23% to 2.15 billion francs from 1.74 billion francs.
The company provisionally estimated its revenue growth for the first nine months of the year at 24.5%. 

The company said it is pursuing a strategy of internal growth with a heavy program of industrial investment to expand production capacity, at the same time trimming production costs to improve its competitive position. 

